1
00:00:01,190 --> 00:00:03,950
Hey, all you viewers out there!

2
00:00:03,950 --> 00:00:07,120
When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make 
sure to keep the room nice and bright,

3
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:09,250
and sit back from the screen, 'kay?

4
00:00:11,690 --> 00:00:15,000
This is... inside of Etherion...?

5
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:17,680
No, it's...

6
00:00:31,250 --> 00:00:32,330
I see now...

7
00:00:33,060 --> 00:00:36,920
I'm dead?

8
00:02:09,370 --> 00:02:11,650
Erza Scarlet...

9
00:02:11,650 --> 00:02:18,610
In God's grace; God fearing; her heart
was as wide as the eternal sky.

10
00:02:18,610 --> 00:02:22,930
Her sword shined nobly for her loved ones...

11
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:30,870
Her figure a dancing, fluttering fairy.
Her beauty was a match for nature itself...

12
00:02:31,450 --> 00:02:37,800
Love makes us stronger, and it is 
love that makes us weak as well...

13
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:39,890
I...

14
00:02:43,390 --> 00:02:44,720
Master...

15
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:48,280
She was like a daughter to me...

16
00:02:51,730 --> 00:02:59,900
The council has decided to award one of the 
two empty council seats to her in perpetuity.

17
00:03:01,470 --> 00:03:06,550
And name Erza Scarlet as one 
of the 10 Wizard Saints.

18
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:10,980
Home.

19
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:18,960
Screw this!

20
00:03:20,170 --> 00:03:23,470
What the hell is everyone doing?

21
00:03:24,300 --> 00:03:25,390
Natsu...

22
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,750
Stop this, Natsu!

23
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,510
Natsu, stop!

24
00:03:31,510 --> 00:03:32,600
Why, you...

25
00:03:32,600 --> 00:03:34,430
Erza ain't dead!

26
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:36,980
Please, Natsu... Stop...

27
00:03:37,860 --> 00:03:40,490
There's no way in hell she's dead!

28
00:03:41,840 --> 00:03:44,660
Face reality, Natsu!

29
00:03:44,660 --> 00:03:45,840
Lemme go!

30
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:48,050
Erza's alive!

31
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:50,570
I...

32
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:55,300
I did this for your future 
and everyone else's, Natsu...

33
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:57,060
And yet...

34
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:01,800
This isn't the future I wanted to see...

35
00:04:02,530 --> 00:04:03,840
I just...

36
00:04:04,450 --> 00:04:06,470
I wanted to see everyone smile...

37
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:08,860
I...

38
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:10,860
...didn't want this...

39
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:24,290
Where am I?

40
00:04:26,820 --> 00:04:29,780
Erza!

41
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:32,880
What happened?

42
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:36,200
I'm... alive?

43
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:40,380
Natsu?

44
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:43,750
You... saved me...

45
00:04:45,810 --> 00:04:49,150
He found me inside that 
vortex of magical power?

46
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:51,750
Incredible...

47
00:04:55,460 --> 00:04:56,530
We're the same.

48
00:04:58,150 --> 00:05:02,220
I couldn't have lived without Fairy Tail.

49
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:07,150
A world without my friends is unthinkable.

50
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:10,650
We're all the same.

51
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:17,620
Never do something like that again.

52
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:19,480
Natsu...

53
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:20,660
Never again!

54
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:25,380
Okay.

55
00:05:26,940 --> 00:05:30,130
Natsu... Thank you.

56
00:05:31,430 --> 00:05:32,870
That's right.

57
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:35,190
You don't die for your friends.

58
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:39,080
You live for your friends!

59
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:48,290
Because that's how you create a happy future!

60
00:05:53,530 --> 00:05:55,700
Is he okay?

61
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:58,040
He's slept for three days straight...

62
00:05:58,870 --> 00:06:01,530
That's what the freak 
gets for eating Etherion.

63
00:06:01,530 --> 00:06:03,450
What'd you just say, Gray?!

64
00:06:03,450 --> 00:06:04,920
He's awake!

65
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,830
He's asleep!

66
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:08,600
If you don't have it in you 
to pick a fight, don't get up!

67
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:13,520
I really caused everyone a lot 
of trouble this time, didn't I?

68
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:16,750
Come on, how many times 
have you said that already?

69
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:19,450
Speaking of which, what happened to her?

70
00:06:19,450 --> 00:06:21,100
Oh, you mean Juvia?

71
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:22,950
She's headed back already.

72
00:06:22,950 --> 00:06:26,780
She said something about wanting to join 
Fairy Tail as soon as possible, or something...

73
00:06:27,310 --> 00:06:28,350
I see.

74
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:33,550
I apologize, Erza.

75
00:06:33,550 --> 00:06:35,620
Sorry, Er-chan.

76
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:40,620
No. It was I who was not able to do 
anything for you for eight years.

77
00:06:41,830 --> 00:06:43,380
I am truly sorry...

78
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:45,210
It's not your fault, Sister!

79
00:06:46,210 --> 00:06:49,400
If I had done something sooner, 
then Simon might have...

80
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,510
Simon was a true man!

81
00:06:52,070 --> 00:06:54,000
He wanted to protect you.

82
00:06:54,530 --> 00:06:55,850
He always...

83
00:06:55,850 --> 00:06:56,900
Wally!

84
00:06:57,390 --> 00:06:59,610
I know well his feelings.

85
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:03,250
As well as the feelings of those left behind.

86
00:07:03,830 --> 00:07:07,080
But we must continue on.

87
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,280
To the future that Simon left for us.

88
00:07:14,140 --> 00:07:17,490
If you have no other place to 
go, then come to Fairy Tail.

89
00:07:19,950 --> 00:07:21,800
Us?

90
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:26,040
It might be different than the 
"freedom" you sought, but...

91
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,760
Salamander did say something like that.

92
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:32,750
That it was one super spiffy guild!

93
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:36,490
And I'd like to stay together with you all.

94
00:07:38,690 --> 00:07:40,280
Come now, let's go back.

95
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:43,290
I have to introduce you all 
properly to Natsu and the others.

96
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:47,400
You've really gotten strong, Erza...

97
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:48,830
Jellal?

98
00:07:57,020 --> 00:07:59,360
It... couldn't be...

99
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:06,660
After that, Erza said something 
to me quietly in private.

100
00:08:07,130 --> 00:08:11,890
She said that it might actually have been 
Jellal who prevented the tower from exploding.

101
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:18,250
Freed from Zeref's possession, he had 
returned to the kind Jellal he once was.

102
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:23,980
He then fused with Etherion in Erza's place 
and directed the magical power up into the sky.

103
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:28,850
It does make a lot of sense 
when you think of it that way.

104
00:08:28,850 --> 00:08:31,350
But it's kind of sad...

105
00:08:31,350 --> 00:08:35,800
It means Jellal was just another 
victim of Zeref's spirit.

106
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:36,900
Lucy!

107
00:08:37,550 --> 00:08:39,080
Have you seen Sho or the others?

108
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:40,840
No, I haven't...

109
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:42,110
I can't find them anywhere.

110
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:48,280
Could they have left without telling anyone?

111
00:08:48,660 --> 00:08:49,810
I see...

112
00:08:49,810 --> 00:08:51,050
What happened?

113
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:56,280
Tell Natsu and Gray to prepare "fireworks."

114
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,040
Huh?

115
00:08:57,040 --> 00:08:58,070
Wait...

116
00:09:00,190 --> 00:09:03,400
Do you really think we 
can make it on our own?

117
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,190
In the outside world?

118
00:09:06,340 --> 00:09:07,740
We have to!

119
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:11,560
We can't bother Sister any more...

120
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:12,780
Everyone!

121
00:09:13,830 --> 00:09:15,070
Sister!

122
00:09:17,670 --> 00:09:21,150
We were raised in the tower our entire lives.

123
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:25,550
There's a lot we don't understand, 
that we're uncertain of...

124
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:29,990
But we want to see the 
outside world for ourselves.

125
00:09:31,270 --> 00:09:34,030
We don't want to live relying 
on others any longer...

126
00:09:34,390 --> 00:09:36,710
We've had enough of living for someone else!

127
00:09:37,650 --> 00:09:40,370
From now on, we'll live for ourselves!

128
00:09:40,370 --> 00:09:42,820
We want to find our own reason to live!

129
00:09:43,510 --> 00:09:45,980
<i>That</i> is our freedom!

130
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:53,360
If you keep that strong will, 
you can accomplish anything.

131
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:55,490
It reassures me.

132
00:09:57,820 --> 00:09:58,730
However...

133
00:09:58,730 --> 00:10:03,150
There are three conditions for 
anyone who leaves Fairy Tail!

134
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:04,490
Listen well.

135
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,290
Leave? But we never even joined...

136
00:10:07,290 --> 00:10:08,360
One!

137
00:10:08,860 --> 00:10:13,250
You must never reveal sensitive information 
about Fairy Tail to others for as long as you live!

138
00:10:13,250 --> 00:10:14,600
Two!

139
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:19,220
You must not have unauthorized contact with 
past clients or profit personally from them!

140
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:20,640
Three!

141
00:10:21,570 --> 00:10:26,870
Even if we walk different paths, one must 
always live on as strong as you are able!

142
00:10:27,350 --> 00:10:32,100
You must never treat your own 
life as something insignificant!

143
00:10:34,110 --> 00:10:39,250
You must never forget the friends 
you love for as long as you live!

144
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:45,800
Begin the Fairy Tail Farewell Ceremony!

145
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:46,450
Yeah!

146
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:56,960
Let bloom the flowers of 
light within your hearts.

147
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:12,300
I wish I could be with you forever...

148
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:19,940
But if that ends up holding you back, then 
I wish to bless your newfound voyage.

149
00:11:19,940 --> 00:11:22,980
You've got it backwards, Er-chan!

150
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:27,160
With us around, you'll be forced 
to remember all the bad things...

151
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:31,800
I won't forget you, no 
matter where you may be.

152
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:35,670
And it is those painful memories 
that become the seeds of tomorrow...

153
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:37,250
They make us stronger...

154
00:11:38,060 --> 00:11:40,360
Humans have that power.

155
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,090
Go on, stronger...

156
00:11:43,090 --> 00:11:45,280
I will continue on, stronger!

157
00:11:47,030 --> 00:11:49,410
If we never forget this 
day, we will meet again.

158
00:11:50,050 --> 00:11:51,230
Stay well.

159
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:52,850
You too, Sis!

160
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,810
Bye-bye, Er-chan!

161
00:11:54,810 --> 00:11:56,370
We'll see each other again!

162
00:11:56,370 --> 00:11:57,940
That's a promise!

163
00:11:59,970 --> 00:12:01,050
It's a promise.

164
00:12:16,310 --> 00:12:17,950
This is a surprise.

165
00:12:17,950 --> 00:12:19,350
They finished it?

166
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:22,590
Our new Fairy Tail!

167
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:25,930
Is this an outdoor cafe?

168
00:12:27,930 --> 00:12:29,640
There's even a goods shop?

169
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:32,010
Welcome! Oh, it's you guys.

170
00:12:32,010 --> 00:12:32,600
Welcome back.

171
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:35,770
Look, you're a salesman now, Max!

172
00:12:35,770 --> 00:12:37,880
And wait, how long has it been again?

173
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:41,130
I've been out studying 
business on Master's orders.

174
00:12:41,130 --> 00:12:43,680
Max Aloze? You've been in Weekly Sorcerer!

175
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:45,150
Since we've just met, glad to be of service.

176
00:12:45,150 --> 00:12:47,410
I've heard quite a lot about you, Lucy.

177
00:12:47,410 --> 00:12:50,280
I don't even want to imagine 
what he's heard about me...

178
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:52,520
Hey, so what are you selling?

179
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:56,010
T-shirts, wrist bands, mugs, towels...

180
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:57,960
And the most popular is...

181
00:12:57,960 --> 00:13:00,250
It's a figure of Lucy!

182
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:02,760
Don't go making something like 
that without my permission!

183
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:04,630
And of course, the clothes are cast-off!

184
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:10,710
How beautiful!

185
00:13:10,710 --> 00:13:13,270
Yes, this is wonderful.

186
00:13:14,630 --> 00:13:16,320
What's the matter, Natsu?

187
00:13:16,320 --> 00:13:17,480
It's different than it was.

188
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,900
Lu-chan, welcome back!

189
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:20,990
Levy-chan!

190
00:13:20,990 --> 00:13:25,300
Great, huh? In the back of 
the drinking hall is a pool!

191
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:26,470
Welcome back!

192
00:13:26,470 --> 00:13:27,810
Why is there a pool?

193
00:13:27,810 --> 00:13:29,070
It's totally different.

194
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:31,770
There's a game parlor in the basement.

195
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:32,510
Yo!

196
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:33,840
You're back?

197
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,230
It's got everything...

198
00:13:35,230 --> 00:13:36,080
It's <i>different</i>.

199
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:38,580
And the biggest change is the second floor.

200
00:13:38,580 --> 00:13:41,220
Anyone can go up there now!

201
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:48,310
Of course you still have to be with an
S-class wizard to go on an S-class quest.

202
00:13:48,310 --> 00:13:51,430
You've returned, you bunch of fools?

203
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:52,600
Master!

204
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:56,450
This is our new member, Juvia.

205
00:13:56,450 --> 00:13:58,370
Ain't she a cutey?

206
00:13:58,370 --> 00:13:59,950
Juvia is glad to be of service!

207
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:03,430
So you really joined?

208
00:14:03,430 --> 00:14:05,280
You helped us a lot at Akane.

209
00:14:05,610 --> 00:14:07,400
It's all thanks to you!

210
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:09,530
Juvia will work hard!

211
00:14:09,530 --> 00:14:11,000
Glad to have you!

212
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,450
Love rival!

213
00:14:12,450 --> 00:14:13,620
Actually, I'm not...

214
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:16,550
And we have one more new member.

215
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:18,510
Come on, say hi to everyone.

216
00:14:19,290 --> 00:14:21,010
There's another one?

217
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,530
Hey!

218
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:24,420
You're got to be joking!

219
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:28,850
Gajeel!

220
00:14:28,850 --> 00:14:30,640
Why is he...

221
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:31,430
Wait!

222
00:14:31,430 --> 00:14:33,100
Juvia recommended him!

223
00:14:34,020 --> 00:14:38,360
Juvia is one thing, but he's the 
very person who destroyed the guild!

224
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:41,030
Now, now...

225
00:14:41,030 --> 00:14:44,250
They say yesterday's enemies 
are tomorrow's friends, yes?

226
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:45,050
Yeah...

227
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:47,440
I d-don't mind at a-all...

228
00:14:48,940 --> 00:14:50,850
This has got to be some joke!

229
00:14:50,850 --> 00:14:52,740
You expect me to go on jobs with this guy?

230
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:54,550
Don't worry.

231
00:14:54,550 --> 00:14:55,740
I ain't sharing my work!

232
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:57,360
Cold as steel!

233
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:59,690
I just want jobs, that's all.

234
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:04,250
I can't believe I ended up here in 
the most annoying guild of all...

235
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,250
Say that again!

236
00:15:05,250 --> 00:15:09,430
Poor Gajeel-kun was always all alone, and 
Juvia couldn't leave him like that, so...

237
00:15:09,430 --> 00:15:12,330
It's not that kind of 
relationship though, really!

238
00:15:12,330 --> 00:15:18,660
It is the role of we elders to guide youth 
from the wrong path to the right one.

239
00:15:18,660 --> 00:15:21,330
Deep down, even he is good.

240
00:15:21,330 --> 00:15:22,560
...or so I'd like to believe.

241
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:26,400
If that's your decision, Master...

242
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:29,600
But I think it best to watch 
him carefully for now.

243
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,770
As you wish.

244
00:15:32,700 --> 00:15:35,950
They're more like dogs 
than dragons, seriously...

245
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:39,180
Yeah! That's even lower than cats!

246
00:15:39,450 --> 00:15:42,150
I just don't feel at home here anymore...

247
00:15:48,220 --> 00:15:49,480
We're back, Mira!

248
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:51,050
Welcome back.

249
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:57,180
I will now sing a song commemorating the 
new guild and to welcome back Natsu's team.

250
00:15:58,810 --> 00:16:00,880
We've been waiting, Mira!

251
00:15:59,780 --> 00:16:01,360
Mira-chan!

252
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:03,100
You're the best, Mirajane!

253
00:16:04,080 --> 00:16:17,390
I brush the desk with you gone...

254
00:16:18,460 --> 00:16:25,750
The shadow drops...

255
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:32,840
Alone again, today...

256
00:16:33,510 --> 00:16:47,230
Looking up at the starry 
sky, I say a prayer...

257
00:16:47,900 --> 00:17:00,550
You are now under this same sky...

258
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:58,070
Glad you all are back...

259
00:17:01,610 --> 00:17:08,790
Even when you're shaking with tears...

260
00:17:08,790 --> 00:17:16,200
Even when it seems like you'll 
be lost to the darkness...

261
00:17:10,310 --> 00:17:14,610
Fairy Tail's children are 
sure to continue to grow...

262
00:17:14,610 --> 00:17:18,680
It may be time for me to 
start thinking about it...

263
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:22,650
Don't forget...

264
00:17:23,260 --> 00:17:29,750
You always have...

265
00:17:30,450 --> 00:17:37,780
You always have a place to return to...

266
00:17:37,780 --> 00:17:53,950
You always have people 
waiting for you to return...

267
00:18:00,640 --> 00:18:03,310
Great! Who's next?

268
00:18:06,310 --> 00:18:07,980
W-What?!

269
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:10,460
I wrote this song myself.

270
00:18:10,460 --> 00:18:12,000
It's called "Best Friend."

271
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:12,980
I hope you like it.

272
00:18:12,980 --> 00:18:14,270
I hope you choke!

273
00:18:14,270 --> 00:18:15,900
And why are you all dolled up in a suit?

274
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,420
Colorful, colorful...

275
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:19,960
Shooby doo bop!

276
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:24,590
Tremble with love, steel grey metallic!

277
00:18:24,590 --> 00:18:25,840
He's got chops!

278
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:27,100
Go for it, Gajeel-kun!

279
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,630
Yeah!

280
00:18:28,630 --> 00:18:31,900
Doo doo doo... Shalala...

281
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:35,850
Shooby doo bop! Shalala...

282
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:41,300
Bite into it, hard! Sweet honey...

283
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:41,180
I've never heard a song this crappy before!

284
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,220
You wanna go?

285
00:18:45,220 --> 00:18:46,720
Shooby do bop!

286
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:48,140
What do you think you're doing?

287
00:18:48,140 --> 00:18:50,140
I'm shooby doo bopping, you jerk!

288
00:18:50,450 --> 00:18:52,110
Stop it!

289
00:18:50,450 --> 00:18:52,110
So annoying...

290
00:18:52,900 --> 00:18:55,600
Who threw that?

291
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:56,530
Natsu!

292
00:18:56,530 --> 00:18:58,570
You're goin' overboard!

293
00:18:58,570 --> 00:19:01,410
My... strawberry cake...

294
00:19:02,380 --> 00:19:03,730
Listen up, you all!

295
00:19:03,730 --> 00:19:05,910
Real men don't make such a damn racket!

296
00:19:05,910 --> 00:19:07,410
Silence!

297
00:19:08,950 --> 00:19:11,210
Somebody stop them!

298
00:19:21,330 --> 00:19:22,800
Now this is more like Fairy Tail...

299
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:32,250
What's the deal calling me out here?

300
00:19:32,250 --> 00:19:35,180
I was thinking about going out on a job...

301
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:37,040
A job?

302
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:38,700
You're the guy who destroyed the guild!

303
00:19:38,700 --> 00:19:40,170
You got no right to a job!

304
00:19:40,170 --> 00:19:42,700
You guys sure are petty.

305
00:19:43,890 --> 00:19:45,520
Stop it...

306
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:50,280
I... don't hold any grudges at all...

307
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:52,410
This is how we...

308
00:19:52,410 --> 00:19:53,870
...settle the score!

309
00:19:55,380 --> 00:19:59,170
You won't be feeling so confident for long!

310
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:01,300
Secret Seeds!

311
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:06,050
Knuckle Plant!

312
00:20:06,850 --> 00:20:08,760
Falcon Heaven's Soar!

313
00:20:14,540 --> 00:20:15,750
Hey...

314
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:17,190
What're you playing at?

315
00:20:18,350 --> 00:20:20,700
What kind of bullying is this?

316
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:24,390
Laxus!

317
00:20:26,960 --> 00:20:31,200
So this is the kid that 
did a number on my guild?

318
00:20:31,780 --> 00:20:36,710
So gramps let someone join to keep 
the guild from being busted up?

319
00:20:38,390 --> 00:20:41,220
That's exactly why people look down on us!

320
00:20:41,220 --> 00:20:42,170
You little piece of...

321
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:49,970
On the road back to town, I heard things in 
bars here and there that really pissed me off.

322
00:20:50,580 --> 00:20:54,230
"Fairy Tail ain't anything special..."?

323
00:20:54,650 --> 00:20:57,650
"Those guys are already through..."?

324
00:21:00,940 --> 00:21:02,970
It's your fault!

325
00:21:11,570 --> 00:21:14,260
Stop, Laxus! That's going too far!

326
00:21:14,260 --> 00:21:16,710
I knew Laxus is crazy strong, but...

327
00:21:16,710 --> 00:21:19,170
It's that one-sided?

328
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:23,680
Wait, is it that Gajeel never even...

329
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:26,800
Because he wanted us to 
recognize him as an ally...

330
00:21:26,800 --> 00:21:28,900
He just took it, without defending himself!

331
00:21:29,970 --> 00:21:34,720
I'll teach you what happens to 
anybody who takes on Fairy Tail!

332
00:21:35,610 --> 00:21:38,160
Stop it, Laxus! That's enough!

333
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:40,400
The weaklings should stay outta this!

334
00:21:48,030 --> 00:21:49,240
Gajeel?

335
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:55,080
You satisfied?

336
00:21:55,840 --> 00:21:57,440
I have work to do.

337
00:22:00,490 --> 00:22:01,380
Um...

338
00:22:01,970 --> 00:22:03,090
Leave me alone.

339
00:22:07,150 --> 00:22:08,650
Idiocy...

340
00:22:09,510 --> 00:22:14,440
This isn't the Fairy Tail I have in mind.

341
00:22:16,050 --> 00:22:18,450
I can't take this any longer!

342
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:23,410
Fairy Tail will be mine!

343
00:23:56,650 --> 00:23:59,130
A tournament to decide the 
strongest in Fairy Tail?

344
00:23:59,130 --> 00:24:00,810
Sounds like fun.

345
00:24:00,810 --> 00:24:03,480
But Erza and Laxus will be in it too!

346
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,370
There's no way you'll win, Natsu.

347
00:24:05,370 --> 00:24:06,490
I like it!

348
00:24:06,490 --> 00:24:08,110
I'll beat 'em all!

349
00:24:08,550 --> 00:24:11,530
Like "gnats" to a flame.

350
00:24:11,530 --> 00:24:12,670
I see!

351
00:24:12,670 --> 00:24:13,970
What?!

352
00:24:13,970 --> 00:24:16,770
Next time: Battle of Fairy Tail!

353
00:24:16,770 --> 00:24:18,470
Now I'm pissed.

354
00:24:18,470 --> 00:24:20,730
I ain't giving you squat when I win, Happy.

355
00:24:20,730 --> 00:24:23,430
Natsu, your temper will be your downfall.

356
00:24:23,430 --> 00:24:24,440
Shut up already!

